entation of the material is presented through a number of concrete examples with an extensive use of graphical visualization. The book is aimed at graduated and post-graduate students and young researchers in theoretical physics, dynamical systems, applied mathematics, solid state physics, crystallography, molecular physics, theoretical chemistry, .  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMathematics. 4aGeneral Physics. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / General.2bisacsh1 aLe Bellac, Michel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLeduc, Michel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2020z97831107564010 cprintz978275981738240uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-1952-2zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759819522zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759819522/original  a978-3-11-075640-1 EDP Sciences Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2020c2016d2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA